    <div class="col">
      <h2>The mandate everyone points at is the small number</h2>
      <p class="reveal">Carriers frame the coming decade as a SAF-cost problem. But run the ReFuelEU blend schedule through the mandate math and the per-passenger cost stays modest for years, and, counter-intuitively, <em>falls</em> when oil is expensive, because a costly fossil baseline shrinks the SAF premium. Set those mandate bars against today's published surcharges and the scale mismatch is the whole point.</p>
    </div>

