    <div class="col">
      <h2>The mechanism is sticky by design</h2>
      <p class="reveal">Trace one carrier's surcharge across twenty-two years and a pattern appears that fuel alone does not explain. It rises fast with the oil price and settles slowly, or not at all. That is not only opportunism. The YQ line exists for distribution reasons: it is exempt from agent commissions, quiet in fare displays, separable from refunds, and outside award-redemption math. The ratchet is what the mechanism is built to produce.</p>
    </div>

