    <!-- PULL-QUOTE -->
    <div class="pullquote reveal">
      <blockquote>A surcharge labelled &ldquo;fuel&rdquo; that contains materially more than fuel is opaque by design.</blockquote>
    </div>

    <!-- REGULATORY FINDINGS -->
    <section class="findings">
      <h2 class="reveal">What the Commission said</h2>
      <div class="finding reveal">
        <div class="finding__pg">Notice, p.3</div>
        <div class="finding__q">&ldquo;Cancellations caused by exceptionally high fuel prices &hellip; cannot be considered &lsquo;extraordinary circumstances&rsquo;.&rdquo;
          <span class="finding__g">High fuel cost is not a defence against EU&nbsp;261 compensation.</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="finding reveal">
        <div class="finding__pg">Notice, p.4</div>
        <div class="finding__q">&ldquo;Any retroactive change of the price is excluded.&rdquo;
          <span class="finding__g">Reg 1008/2008 locks price at point of sale; post-sale YQ changes must go.</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="finding reveal">
        <div class="finding__pg">Notice, p.6</div>
        <div class="finding__q">&ldquo;The cost of jet fuel can in principle not be considered a serious disturbance of operations giving rise to JNUS.&rdquo;
          <span class="finding__g">Fuel cost is not a slot-waiver justification.</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="finding reveal">
        <div class="finding__pg">Notice, p.7</div>
        <div class="finding__q">&ldquo;These are not &hellip; relevant justifications for the use of exemptions under Article 5(2) RFEUA.&rdquo;
          <span class="finding__g">The tankering loophole is foreclosed pre-emptively. The SAF timeline holds.</span></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- METHOD -->
    <section class="rigor">
      <h2>Method &amp; where this can be challenged</h2>
      <p><b>The one-line method.</b> Fair pass-through is the per-passenger fuel cost recovered at the hedge-adjusted price move; the gap above it is everything else, currency, ETS/CORSIA, distribution, disruption, recovered under a single label called &ldquo;fuel.&rdquo;</p>
      <p><b>The honest limitation.</b> Every multiplier is scaled from one disclosed hedge book and carries roughly &plusmn;10&ndash;20 points per carrier. The directional finding is robust; the specific numbers are best-estimate, not precise. The Gulf 13&times; in particular is a median across a 4&ndash;19&times; range.</p>
      <p>The full derivations, the four-column Gulf sensitivity matrix, the primary-source table, and the glossary live in the methodology paper of record, available on request.</p>
    </section>
  </main>

